Tuskegee University counted at least 100 lynchings in North Carolina between 1882 and 1968.

Despite over 200 attempts, lynching has never been designated a federal hate crime. 

@RepBobbyRush’s Emmett Till #AntilynchingAct changes that — and today, @POTUS is signing it into law.

Today is a giant step forward for Black Maternal Health.

@FrankPallone &amp; @EnergyCommerce just approved #BuildBackBetter Act legislation that includes historic investments from @BMHCaucus' #Momnibus legislation! 

